result.execSummary:
The defendant Mitch Charles Erwin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Mitch Charles Erwin in court with attorney Dianne Margaret Erickson.  Defendant Mitch Charles Erwin in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Case scheduled for jury trial.  Parties have reached a resolution and are prepared to proceed with plea and sentencing.  

As to Count 1:   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the Defendant guilty and enters judgment of conviction into the record forthwith. 

As to Counts 2 and 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Counts 2 and 3 DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.  


Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.  Additional statements by victim. 

As to Count 1:    The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 42 months, credit for 99 days time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 18 months, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 months. Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 3 years.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Serve 6 months in HOC as Condition Time, 5 months, STAYED pending review; 30 days to be served FORTHWITH with Huber for work.

-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.

-No contact with victim S.B. without the approval of the court/agent.
